issue.title: There are some problems in Python/Counting-sort.py
issue.body:
If you enter a float to element, this program would return a ValueError because of invalid literal for int(). This is ok. It can be fixed by adding error judge. 
But if you enter a negative number to element, there would not have a error warning. It causes by Python‘s special grammar.
```Python
l = [1,2,3,4,5]
print(l[-4])
```
The result will be 2. So I think there should add some ways to avoid this situation.
I am poor in English. I hope you understand.
